, whereas the nitrogen chemistry may be strongly\naffected by cosmic ray ionization. The [C II] 158 $\\mu$m line is well\nreproduced by our models and its ``deficit'' relative to the CII/FIR ratio in\nnormal and starburst galaxies is suggested to be mainly a consequence of the\ndominant non-PDR component of far-infrared radiation, although our models alone\ncannot rule out extinction effects in the nuclei.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jun 2004 18:03:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-16"}
